    {
      "id": "60d77118-d197-407a-8454-24dea339040f",
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "Example 4 (functions, conditionals, and statement blocks): Write the equivalent Java code for the Python program below\n\n    def max3(x, y, z):\n        if x > y or z > y:\n            if x > z:\n                return x\n            else:\n                return z\n        else:\n            return y\n\n    print(max3(1, 2, 3))\n    print(max3(4, 6, 2))\n    print(max3(10, 5, 1))\n",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "markdown",
        "id": "60d77118-d197-407a-8454-24dea339040f"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "1ba56cfe-dc7a-4f8f-be7a-aa3709596763",
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "int max3(int x, int y, int z){\r\n    if ((x > y) || (z>y)){\r\n        if (x> z) {return x;}\r\n        else{return z;}\r\n    }\r\n    else{return y;}\r\n}\r\n\r\nIO.println(max3(1,2,3));\r\nIO.println(max3(4, 6, 2));\r\nIO.println(max3(10, 5, 1));",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "java",
        "id": "1ba56cfe-dc7a-4f8f-be7a-aa3709596763",
        "executionSummary": {
          "executionOrder": 50,
          "success": true
        }
      },
      "execution_count": 50,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "execute_result",
          "data": {
            "text/plain": "3\r\n6\r\n10\r\n"
          },
          "metadata": {},
          "execution_count": 50
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "c6bc68e3-ca08-4be7-b4c1-454ca4dda70f",
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "Example 5 (comments): Write the equivalent Java code for the Python program below\n    t = 0 # Reset the clock\n\n    fSun = 100.4\n    fSunEarth = 20.5\n\n    # In Earth-centered frame, must substract\n    # Sun' gravity at Earth's center\n    fSun = fSun - fSunEarth\n\n    def reciprocal(x):\n        \"\"\" Return 1 divided by the argument\"\"\"\n        return 1/x\n\n    print(reciprocal(fSun))",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "markdown",
        "id": "c6bc68e3-ca08-4be7-b4c1-454ca4dda70f"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "e42f1a81-87ed-4c08-acb2-46ac3a371835",
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "int t = 0; // Reset the clock\r\n\r\ndouble  fSun = 100.4;\r\ndouble fSunEarth = 20.5;\r\n\r\nfSun = fSun - fSunEarth;\r\n\r\n// In Earth-centered frame, must substract\r\n//  Sun' gravity at Earth's center\r\n\r\ndouble reciproca1(double x){\r\n    /* Return 1 divided by the argument*/ \r\n    return 1/x;\r\n}\r\nIO.println(reciproca1(fSun));\r\n",
      "metadata": {
