    {
      "id": "1b375df1-5aa9-49ae-9bd5-439079b7cf3c",
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "Example 8 (chained conditionals): Write the equivalent Java code for the Python program below\n\n    # Chained conditional\n\n    def print_letter_grade(score):\n        if score >= 90:\n            print(\"Grade A\")\n        elif score >= 80:\n            print(\"Grade B\")\n        elif score >= 70:\n            print(\"Grade C\")\n        else:\n            print(\"Grade D or below\")\n\n    print_letter_grade(96)\n    print_letter_grade(85)\n    print_letter_grade(70)\n    print_letter_grade(63)",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "markdown",
        "id": "1b375df1-5aa9-49ae-9bd5-439079b7cf3c"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "6794bc2c-411a-4ad4-bef6-ae3918336108",
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "//Chained conditional\r\n\r\n    void print_letter_grade(int score){\r\n        if (score >= 90){\r\n            IO.println(\"Grade A\");}\r\n        else if (score >= 80){\r\n            IO.println(\"Grade B\");}\r\n        else if (score >= 70){\r\n            IO.println(\"Grade C\");}\r\n        else{\r\n            IO.println(\"Grade D or below\");}\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    print_letter_grade(96);\r\n    print_letter_grade(85);\r\n    print_letter_grade(70);\r\n    print_letter_grade(63);",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "java",
        "id": "6794bc2c-411a-4ad4-bef6-ae3918336108",
        "executionSummary": {
          "executionOrder": 74,
          "success": true
        }
      },
      "execution_count": 74,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "execute_result",
          "data": {
            "text/plain": "Grade A\r\nGrade B\r\nGrade C\r\nGrade D or below\r\n"
          },
          "metadata": {},
          "execution_count": 74
        }
      ]
    },
